ly cited as the crucial starting point in understanding the Haitian revolution, Colonialism and Science will be welcomed by students and scholars alike. “By deftly weaving together imperialism and science in the story of French colonialism, [McClellan] . . . brings to light the history of an almost forgotten colony.”—Journal of Modern History “McClellan has produced an impressive case study offering excellent surveys of Saint Domingue’s colonial history and its history of science.”—Isis  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  ascience, colonialism, empire, colonies, race, wealth, natural resources, haiti, saint domingue, history, politics, economics, nonfiction, haitian revolution, imperialism, france, freemasonry, cercle des philadelphes, meteorology, botany, zoology, biology, nature, environment, medicine, expedition, discovery, research, experimentation, naturalists, missionary, religion.1 aSaint-Louis, Vertus.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226514680423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226514680/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles